modules.description: This module handles IP geolocation lookups and credit checks via a web service API. It works with IP addresses and JSON responses, providing structured data retrieval for location-based queries. Concrete use cases include determining geographic locations of IP addresses and checking API usage credits.

This module provides functions to open and query a binary IP geolocation database, retrieving detailed location and network information for IPv4 and IPv6 addresses. It works with structured metadata and IP records containing fields like country, region, ISP, latitude, longitude, and more. Concrete use cases include IP-based geolocation lookup for web analytics, content localization, and network troubleshooting.

This module enables IP geolocation lookups through both a web service API and a local binary database, supporting IPv4 and IPv6 addresses. It provides structured data retrieval for location and network information such as country, region, ISP, latitude, and longitude, along with API credit checks. You can use it to determine the geographic origin of an IP, localize content, analyze web traffic, or troubleshoot network issues. Examples include querying a database for the country associated with an IP or checking remaining API credits before making a remote lookup.
